parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust manifold bolts can cause exhaust fumes to leak into the passenger compartment, posing a health risk to occupants. It can also lead to warping of the exhaust manifold and crossover pipe, requiring costly repairs.
symptoms: Exhaust fumes leaking into the vehicle
warping of the exhaust manifold and crossover pipe.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft can cause the engine to shut down, leading to loss of power and control, which can result in accidents. It can also lead to costly repairs and replacement of the engine.
The failure of the motor mounts can cause excessive engine movement, leading to premature wear on other engine components and potentially causing engine damage.
symptoms: broken or worn out motor mounts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the head gasket can cause engine damage, overheating, and loss of power, which can lead to accidents. It can also result in costly repairs and replacement of the engine.
The failure of the timing belt can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs and replacement of the engine. It can also result in loss of power and control, which can lead to accidents.

especially when the heater or air conditioning is on

fuel leaking from the fuel rail
